    {
      "id": "1",
      "dateLeft": "July 25, 1937",
      "textLeft": "The truth is, I didn't expect to leave San Esteban and see the world in this way, although the last few years had been confusing for everyone. With the war now between the nationalists and the reds, military service became indispensable and inevitable, at least for those of us on the nationalist side.",
      "dateRight": "July 25, 1937",
      "textRight": "While some fight for the ideals of one side or the other, I am reluctant to all of this. I have never been much of a churchgoer, and I leave politics to those who are eager to get involved in fights."
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "dateLeft": "July 25, 1937",
      "textLeft": "I know that I could end up arrested for these words, and the truth is, I don't care. Today, on July 25, 1937, I leave San Esteban De Gormaz for the Soria recruitment center by train. I have only one goal, to return home.",
      "dateRight": "July 25, 1937",
      "textRight": "I have never been in the war, but those from the village who have been tell me that if I obey the commands, keep my head down, and stay with my squad, I will get through this."
    }
  ]
}

