{
  "id": "Entrada2-1",
  "paginas": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "dateLeft": "August 5",
      "textLeft": "It's been a few days since I arrived at my unit's barracks. After about 10 days in Soria, on August 5, they sent me to Zaragoza. Now, I am a soldier in the national army, Battalion 103 belonging to Division 105. However, I haven't reached my unit yet.",
      "dateRight": "August 5",
      "textRight": "The captain who received us told us that we would be here for two weeks. After that, we would be assigned to our units as replacements, reinforcements, or simply new troops for new units."
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "dateLeft": "August 5",
      "textLeft": "So far, the only thing we've done is learn how to communicate with the officers, and we've fired a couple of shots. I still haven't fully gotten used to shooting; the recoil of the butt leaves my shoulder a bit sore after a few shots.",
      "dateRight": "August 5",
      "textRight": "The sergeant says it's common and that after we fire a bit more and know how to use them well, we won't feel the pain anymore."
    }
  ]
}

